- ^^**Battle of Wandiwash = 22 January 1760**^^
    - Between French and British
    - at Vandavasi , Tamil Nadu
    - result British won
        - **Aftermath**
            - The Battle of Wandiwash resulted in the British capture of Chetpattu ([Chetpet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chetpet) ), Tirunomalai ([Thiruvannaamalai](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thiruvannaamalai) ), [Tindivanam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tindivanam)  and [Perumukkal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perumukkal) .[[3]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Wandiwash#cite_note-sdgfasdfe-3)  As a consequence of the engagement, the French in South India, under the command of general [Marquis de Bussy-Castelnau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marquis_de_Bussy-Castelnau) , were then restricted to [Pondichéry](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pondicherry_district) , where they surrendered on 22 January 1761. The collapse of the French position in India was one of the events that compelled France to sign the [Treaty of Paris](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1763) ), reducing the French to little more than traders in India, and effectively ending further French imperial ambitions in that country. Britain, on the other hand, established its supremacy in India over other European powers after this battle.
